    <string name="sehri_info_title">Sehri, Imsak &amp; Iftar</string>
    <string name="sehri_info_body">Sehri (the pre-dawn meal) ends at Fajr, so you can eat right up to true dawn. Imsak is a precaution about 10 minutes before Fajr, to stop early and be safe. Iftar is at Maghrib, when you break your fast.</string>
    <string name="sehri_info_regions">All four schools hold the true cutoff is Fajr, so most Muslims stop then. Following Imsak is more a regional custom, common in South Asia, Turkey and Indonesia, while the Gulf and much of the Arab world eat until Fajr. Both are valid, so pick what you follow.</string>
